text.tspan: Journal of Empty Lives and Letter Openers *
* Proposed
20 years from now, when your kids ask you
what you were doing when Tort Bunny kicked
a senator in the balls, wouldn't you like
to say "Bluebooking"?

* Proposed
20 years from now, when your kids ask you
what you were doing when Tort Bunny kicked
a senator in the balls, wouldn't you like
to say "Bluebooking"?
Join our journal!
Join our club!
We offer bonds fraternal.
And awesome grub!
In drinking games,
we can't be beat!
Our outline bank
is most complete.
Will you join--
--our special few?
Yes I will! Yes I do.
Then prove to us your will be true.
By paying now required dues!
Forty dollars!
Pay it now!
Fifty!
Pay it quickly!
Don't delay and wait 'til 'morrow
Or treble dues shall be your sorrow.
Of course I will! Of course I must!
I'll do anything to earn your trust.
Our alumni all know fortune and fame.
Except those who don't,
but they were lame.
Oh this group sounds really swell.
Are you here to pay as well?
2Ls don't pay dues.
Oh, that was supposed
to rhyme, wasn't it?
Cite as: Andrew Fong, Your dues do be due, TORT BUNNIES (September 6, 2010), http://tortbunnies.com/50.html.
